frameDefinitions: An Agent supports their body in a particular Location.
The Sleeper stays in an altered state of consciousness with greatly reduced external awareness.
This frame covers words for Body_part(s) (BP) belonging to a Possessor (Poss), which may be characterized by a Descriptor (Desc).
A Protagonist changes the overall position and posture of the body.
A Reader visually examines a Text, typically in a linear order, to understand its content.
An Agent acts in a certain Manner either generally or under some particular Circumstances.
frameExamples: He had to brace his right <t><fex name='Body_part'>arm</fex></t> against his leg in order to fight the roll.
Smithers <t>leaned</t> forward to grab the folder on the far side.
He pledges to  <t>conduct</t> himself  with honesty and humility.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the individual whose body is in a particular posture.  The <fen>Agent</fen> role is generally expressed as the external argument of verbs:
A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen>.  The <fen>Location</fen> of the <fen>Agent</fen> is frequently expressed and generally occurs as a PP Complement:
The part of the body that provides support to the <fen>Agent</fen>'s body in the posture.
This role indicates the Time interval during which the <fen>Agent</fen> held a certain posture.
The entity that is sleeping.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the sleep occurs.
Where the event takes place.
This Frame Element denotes the <fen>Possessor</fen> of the <fen>Body_part</fen>.
This Frame Element  is the <fen>Body_part</fen>.
The individual whose posture changes.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> changes posture.
The one who examines a <fen>Text</fen> to understand it.
The entity that contains linguistic symbols.
The idea that an implicit <fen>Text</fen> or texts focuses on.
When the reading event takes place.
Where the reading event takes place.
This role marks expressions that denote the person whose conduct is being evaluated.
This role marks expressions that characterize the way that the <fen>Agent</fen> behaves.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> behaves in a certain way.
The location at which the <fen>Agent</fen> exhibits their behavior.
